com.coveros.selenified.utilities

Class Reporter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.coveros.selenified.utilities.Reporter

  • public class Reporter
extends Object
    A custom output file, recording all details of every step performed, both actions and app. Actions, expected results, and actual results are captured. All asserts have a screenshot taken for traceability, while all failing actions also have a screenshot taken to assist with debugging purposes
    Version:
    3.3.0
    Author:
    Max Saperstone

                String version,
                String objectives)
         throws InvalidBrowserException,
                InvalidProxyException
        Creates a new instance of the Reporter, which will serve as the detailed log
        Parameters:
        directory - - a string of the directory holding the files
        test - - a string value of the test name, typically the method name
        capabilities - - the capabilities of the tests that are running
        url - - the url all of the tests are running against
        suite - - the test suite associated with the particular test
        groups - - any testng groups associated with the particular test
        author - - the author associated with the particular test
        version - - the version of the test suite associated with the particular test
        objectives - - the test objectives, taken from the testng description
        Throws:
        InvalidBrowserException
        InvalidProxyException

      • pass

        public void pass(String check,
                 double waitFor,
                 String actual,
                 double timeTook)
        Records the performed check as a pass to the output file. A screenshot will be taken for traceability This method takes in a check being performed, and determines if a wait is occurring or not. If no wait, no action is recorded. If a wait was performed, that wait is added to the check, and recorded as the action. The check is used as the expected outcome, and the actual input is used for actual. If it took some time (timeTook greater than zero), than the actual result will be updated to reflect the time took. If a 'real' browser is not being used (not NONE or HTMLUNIT), then no screenshot will be taken
        Parameters:
        check - - the check being performed
        waitFor - - how long was something waited for. Provide 0 if no wait, and therefore no action
        actual - - the actual outcome from the check
        timeTook - - how long something took to run, provide 0 if it was an immediate check, and actual will be returned unaltered

      • fail

        Records the performed check as a fail to the output file. A screenshot will be taken for traceability This method takes in a check being performed, and determines if a wait is occurring or not. If no wait, no action is recorded. If a wait was performed, that wait is added to the check, and recorded as the action. The check is used as the expected outcome, and the actual input is used for actual. If it took some time (timeTook greater than zero), than the actual result will be updated to reflect the time took. If a 'real' browser is not being used (not NONE or HTMLUNIT), then no screenshot will be taken
        Parameters:

        waitFor - - how long was something waited for. Provide 0 if no wait, and therefore no action
